0:11:25.26,000 --> 0:11:28,000
The last time CO2 was 390 ppm,

268
0:11:28.26,000 --> 0:11:3,000
today's value,

269
0:11:30.26,000 --> 0:11:32,000
sea level was higher

270
0:11:32.26,000 --> 0:11:35,000
by at least 15 meters, 50 feet.

271
0:11:35.26,000 --> 0:11:37,000
Where you are sitting now

272
0:11:37.26,000 --> 0:11:39,000
would be under water.

273
0:11:39.26,000 --> 0:11:42,000
Most estimates are that, this century,

274
0:11:42.26,000 --> 0:11:44,000
we will get at least one meter.

275
0:11:44.26,000 --> 0:11:46,000
I think it will be more

276
0:11:46.26,000 --> 0:11:48,000
if we keep burning fossil fuels,

277
0:11:48.26,000 --> 0:11:51,000
perhaps even five meters, which is 18 feet,

278
0:11:51.26,000 --> 0:11:54,000
this century or shortly thereafter.

279
0:11:54.26,000 --> 0:11:56,000
The important point

280
0:11:56.26,000 --> 0:11:59,000
is that we will have started a process

281
0:11:59.26,000 --> 0:12:02,000
that is out of humanity's control.

282
0:12:02.26,000 --> 0:12:05,000
Ice sheets would continue to disintegrate for centuries.

283
0:12:05.26,000 --> 0:12:07,000
There would be no stable shoreline.

284
0:12:07.26,000 --> 0:12:1,000
The economic consequences are almost unthinkable.

285
0:12:10.26,000 --> 0:12:14,000
Hundreds of New Orleans-like devastations

286
0:12:14.26,000 --> 0:12:16,000
around the world.

287
0:12:16.26,000 --> 0:12:18,000
What may be more reprehensible,

288
0:12:18.26,000 --> 0:12:2,000
if climate denial continues,

289
0:12:20.26,000 --> 0:12:22,000
is extermination of species.

290
0:12:22.26,000 --> 0:12:24,000
The monarch butterfly

291
0:12:24.26,000 --> 0:12:29,000
could be one of the 20 to 50 percent of all species

292
0:12:29.26,000 --> 0:12:32,000
that the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change estimates

293
0:12:32.26,000 --> 0:12:34,000
will be ticketed for extinction

294
0:12:34.26,000 --> 0:12:36,000
by the end of the century

295
0:12:36.26,000 --> 0:12:4,000
if we stay on business-as-usual fossil fuel use.

296
0:12:40.26,000 --> 0:12:43,000
Global warming is already affecting people.

297
0:12:43.26,000 --> 0:12:45,000
The Texas, Oklahoma, Mexico

298
0:12:45.26,000 --> 0:12:48,000
heatwave and drought last year,

299
0:12:48.26,000 --> 0:12:5,000
Moscow the year before

300
0:12:50.26,000 --> 0:12:52,000
and Europe in 2003,

301
0:12:52.26,000 --> 0:12:55,000
were all exceptional events,

302
0:12:55.26,000 --> 0:12:59,000
more than three standard deviations outside the norm.

303
0:12:59.26,000 --> 0:13:01,000
Fifty years ago,

304
0:13:01.26,000 --> 0:13:03,000
such anomalies

305
0:13:03.26,000 --> 0:13:05,000
covered only two- to three-tenths

306
0:13:05.26,000 --> 0:13:07,000
of one percent of the land area.

307
0:13:07.26,000 --> 0:13:09,000
In recent years,

308
0:13:09.26,000 --> 0:13:11,000
because of global warming,

309
0:13:11.26,000 --> 0:13:13,000
they now cover about 10 percent --

310
0:13:13.26,000 --> 0:13:16,000
an increase by a factor of 25 to 50.

311
0:13:16.26,000 --> 0:13:19,000
So we can say with a high degree of confidence

312
0:13:19.26,000 --> 0:13:21,000
that the severe Texas and Moscow heatwaves

313
0:13:21.26,000 --> 0:13:23,000
were not natural;

314
0:13:23.26,000 --> 0:13:26,000
they were caused by global warming.

315
0:13:26.26,000 --> 0:13:28,000
An important impact,

316
0:13:28.26,000 --> 0:13:3,000
if global warming continues,

317
0:13:30.26,000 --> 0:13:33,000
will be on the breadbasket of our nation and the world,

318
0:13:33.26,000 --> 0:13:35,000
the Midwest and Great Plains,

319
0:13:35.26,000 --> 0:13:38,000
which are expected to become prone to extreme droughts,

320
0:13:38.26,000 --> 0:13:4,000
worse than the Dust Bowl,

321
0:13:40.26,000 --> 0:13:42,000
within just a few decades,

322
0:13:42.26,000 --> 0:13:46,000
if we let global warming continue.

323
0:13:46.26,000 --> 0:13:49,000
How did I get dragged deeper and deeper

324
0:13:49.26,000 --> 0:13:51,000
into an attempt to communicate,

325
0:13:51.26,000 --> 0:13:54,000
giving talks in 10 countries, getting arrested,

326
0:13:54.26,000 --> 0:13:56,000
burning up the vacation time

327
0:13:56.26,000 --> 0:13:59,000
that I had accumulated over 30 years?

328
0:14:00.26,000 --> 0:14:03,000
More grandchildren helped me along.

329
0:14:03.26,000 --> 0:14:05,000
Jake is a super-positive,

330
0:14:05.26,000 --> 0:14:08,000
enthusiastic boy.

331
0:14:08.26,000 --> 0:14:1,000
Here at age two and a half years,

332
0:14:10.26,000 --> 0:14:12,000
he thinks he can protect

333
0:14:12.26,000 --> 0:14:15,000
his two and a half-day-old little sister.

334
0:14:15.26,000 --> 0:14:17,000
It would be immoral

335
0:14:17.26,000 --> 0:14:19,000
to leave these young people

336
0:14:19.26,000 --> 0:14:21,000
with a climate system

337
0:14:21.26,000 --> 0:14:23,000
spiraling out of control.

338
0:14:23.26,000 --> 0:14:26,000
Now the tragedy about climate change

339
0:14:26.26,000 --> 0:14:28,000
is that we can solve it

340
0:14:28.26,000 --> 0:14:3,000
with a simple, honest approach

341
0:14:30.26,000 --> 0:14:33,000
of a gradually rising carbon fee

342
0:14:33.26,000 --> 0:14:35,000
collected from fossil fuel companies

343
0:14:35.26,000 --> 0:14:39,000
and distributed 100 percent electronically

344
0:14:39.26,000 --> 0:14:41,000
every month to all legal residents

345
0:14:41.26,000 --> 0:14:43,000
on a per capita basis,

346
0:14:43.26,000 --> 0:14:47,000
with the government not keeping one dime.

347
0:14:47.26,000 --> 0:14:5,000
Most people would get more in the monthly dividend

348
0:14:50.26,000 --> 0:14:52,000
than they'd pay in increased prices.

349
0:14:52.26,000 --> 0:14:54,000
This fee and dividend

350
0:14:54.26,000 --> 0:14:56,000
would stimulate the economy

351
0:14:56.26,000 --> 0:14:58,000
and innovations,

352
0:14:58.26,000 --> 0:15:,000
creating millions of jobs.

353
0:15:00.26,000 --> 0:15:02,000
It is the principal requirement

354
0:15:02.26,000 --> 0:15:05,000
for moving us rapidly

355
0:15:05.26,000 --> 0:15:07,000
to a clean energy future.

356
0:15:07.26,000 --> 0:15:09,000
Several top economists

357
0:15:09.26,000 --> 0:15:12,000
are coauthors on this proposition.

358
0:15:12.26,000 --> 0:15:15,000
Jim DiPeso of Republicans for Environmental Protection

359
0:15:15.26,000 --> 0:15:17,000
describes it thusly:

360
0:15:17.26,000 --> 0:15:19,000
"Transparent. Market-based.

361
0:15:19.26,000 --> 0:15:21,000
Does not enlarge government.

362
0:15:21.26,000 --> 0:15:24,000
Leaves energy decisions to individual choices.

363
0:15:24.26,000 --> 0:15:28,000
Sounds like a conservative climate plan."

364
0:15:28.26,000 --> 0:15:32,000
But instead of placing a rising fee on carbon emissions

365
0:15:32.26,000 --> 0:15:35,000
to make fossil fuels pay

366
0:15:35.26,000 --> 0:15:37,000
their true cost to society,

367
0:15:37.26,000 --> 0:15:4,000
our governments are forcing the public

368
0:15:40.26,000 --> 0:15:43,000
to subsidize fossil fuels

369
0:15:43.26,000 --> 0:15:46,000
by 400 to 500 billion dollars

370
0:15:46.26,000 --> 0:15:48,000
per year worldwide,

371
0:15:48.26,000 --> 0:15:51,000
thus encouraging extraction of every fossil fuel --

372
0:15:51.26,000 --> 0:15:53,000
mountaintop removal,

373
0:15:53.26,000 --> 0:15:55,000
longwall mining, fracking,

374
0:15:55.26,000 --> 0:15:57,000
tar sands, tar shale,

375
0:15:57.26,000 --> 0:16:,000
deep ocean Arctic drilling.

376
0:16:00.26,000 --> 0:16:02,000
This path, if continued,

377
0:16:02.26,000 --> 0:16:05,000
guarantees that we will pass tipping points

378
0:16:05.26,000 --> 0:16:07,000
leading to ice sheet disintegration

379
0:16:07.26,000 --> 0:16:11,000
that will accelerate out of control of future generations.

380
0:16:11.26,000 --> 0:16:13,000
A large fraction of species

381
0:16:13.26,000 --> 0:16:15,000
will be committed to extinction.

382
0:16:15.26,000 --> 0:16:17,000
And increasing intensity of droughts and floods

383
0:16:17.26,000 --> 0:16:2,000
will severely impact breadbaskets of the world,

384
0:16:20.26,000 --> 0:16:22,000
causing massive famines

385
0:16:22.26,000 --> 0:16:25,000
and economic decline.

386
0:16:26.26,000 --> 0:16:29,000
Imagine a giant asteroid

387
0:16:29.26,000 --> 0:16:33,000
on a direct collision course with Earth.

388
0:16:33.26,000 --> 0:16:35,000
That is the equivalent

389
0:16:35.26,000 --> 0:16:37,000
of what we face now.

390
0:16:37.26,000 --> 0:16:39,000
Yet, we dither,

391
0:16:39.26,000 --> 0:16:41,000
taking no action

392
0:16:41.26,000 --> 0:16:43,000
to divert the asteroid,

393
0:16:43.26,000 --> 0:16:45,000
even though the longer we wait,

394
0:16:45.26,000 --> 0:16:49,000
the more difficult and expensive it becomes.

395
0:16:49.26,000 --> 0:16:51,000
If we had started in 2005,

396
0:16:51.26,000 --> 0:16:54,000
it would have required emission reductions of three percent per year

397
0:16:54.26,000 --> 0:16:57,000
to restore planetary energy balance

398
0:16:57.26,000 --> 0:17:,000
and stabilize climate this century.

399
0:17:00.26,000 --> 0:17:02,000
If we start next year,

400
0:17:02.26,000 --> 0:17:04,000
it is six percent per year.

401
0:17:04.26,000 --> 0:17:07,000
If we wait 10 years, it is 15 percent per year --

402
0:17:07.26,000 --> 0:17:09,000
extremely difficult and expensive,

403
0:17:09.26,000 --> 0:17:12,000
perhaps impossible.

404
0:17:12.26,000 --> 0:17:14,000
But we aren't even starting.

405
0:17:14.26,000 --> 0:17:17,000
So now you know what I know

406
0:17:17.26,000 --> 0:17:2,000
that is moving me to sound this alarm.

407
0:17:20.26,000 --> 0:17:23,000
Clearly, I haven't gotten this message across.

408
0:17:23.26,000 --> 0:17:26,000
The science is clear.

409
0:17:26.26,000 --> 0:17:28,000
I need your help

410
0:17:28.26,000 --> 0:17:3,000
to communicate the gravity and the urgency

411
0:17:30.26,000 --> 0:17:32,000
of this situation

412
0:17:32.26,000 --> 0:17:34,000
and its solutions

413
0:17:34.26,000 --> 0:17:36,000
more effectively.

414
0:17:36.26,000 --> 0:17:38,000
We owe it to our children and grandchildren.

